  "text": "Preparation of sciatic nerve sections and teased fibers. Teased fibers and frozen sections from sciatic and optic nerves were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, sciatic nerves were removed from Sprague Dawley rats (Taconic Farms, Germantown, NY), fixed in 4% paraformaldehyde, and teased in ice-cold Dulbecco's PBS using fine needles. For frozen sections, sciatic nerves were dissected out, fixed in 4% paraformaldehyde, cryoprotected in 30% sucrose, frozen in OCT (VWR Scientific Products New York, NY), and cut in 10 m thick cryostat sections. Tissue slides were stored at Ϫ80°C until used.",
